column1: #Text=The Indiana Pacers ( 10 - 5 ) defeated the Chicago Bulls ( 9 - 5 ) 104 - 92 on Wednesday at Bankers Life Fieldhouse in Indianapolis .

#Text=The Pacers were the superior shooters in this one , going 43 percent from the field and 29 percent from the three - point line , while the Bulls went just 35 percent from the floor and a meager 42 percent from beyond the arc .

#Text=The Pacers were led by Paul George , who went 11 - for - 24 from the field and 4 - for - 10 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 33 points , while also adding eight rebounds and two blocked shots .
#Text=He 000s now averaging 13 points and 4 rebounds on the season .
#Text=Jimmy Butler also had a double - double of his own , finishing with 16 points ( 4 - 10 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt , 6 - 6 FT ) , five rebounds , five assists and two steals .
